01:03:38.830 --> 01:03:40.762
and meaning of dreams, et cetera.

01:03:40.762 --> 01:03:43.130
You know, there's not a lot of hard data

01:03:43.130 --> 01:03:43.980
about how to do this,

01:03:43.980 --> 01:03:47.240
but a lot of people report
keeping a sleep journal,

01:03:47.240 --> 01:03:49.320
where a dream journal can be very useful.

01:03:49.320 --> 01:03:51.360
So they mark when they
think they fell asleep

01:03:51.360 --> 01:03:53.230
the night before, when they woke up

01:03:53.230 --> 01:03:55.350
and if they wake up in
the middle of the night,

01:03:55.350 --> 01:03:57.404
early in the morning
they'll just write down

01:03:57.404 --> 01:03:59.700
what they can recall of their dreams.

01:03:59.700 --> 01:04:01.910
And even if they recall nothing,

01:04:01.910 --> 01:04:04.640
many people have the
experience of mid morning

01:04:04.640 --> 01:04:07.210
or later afternoon that
suddenly comes to them

01:04:07.210 --> 01:04:10.150
that they had a dream about
something and writing that down.

01:04:10.150 --> 01:04:11.860
I kept a dream journal for a while.

01:04:11.860 --> 01:04:13.340
It didn't really afford me much.

01:04:13.340 --> 01:04:14.950
I didn't really learn anything

01:04:14.950 --> 01:04:17.050
except that my dreams were very bizarre.

01:04:17.050 --> 01:04:20.345
But, there are some things
that happen in dreams

01:04:20.345 --> 01:04:22.880
that are associated with REM sleep

01:04:22.880 --> 01:04:24.320
as compared to slow wave sleep,

01:04:24.320 --> 01:04:25.640
which can tell you whether or not

01:04:25.640 --> 01:04:28.980
your dream likely happened in
REM sleep or slow wave sleep.

01:04:28.980 --> 01:04:30.900
And the distinguishing
feature it turns out

01:04:30.900 --> 01:04:33.348
is something called theory of mind.

01:04:33.348 --> 01:04:35.020
Theory of mind is actually an idea

01:04:35.020 --> 01:04:38.500
that was developed for the
study and assessment of autism.

01:04:38.500 --> 01:04:42.189
And it was initially that
phrase, theory of mind,

01:04:42.189 --> 01:04:47.070
was brought about by Simon Baron Cohen,

01:04:47.070 --> 01:04:51.042
who is Sacha Baron Cohen,
the comedians brother.

01:04:51.042 --> 01:04:54.484
Simon Baron Cohen is a psychologist and

01:04:54.484 --> 01:04:58.510
to some extent an
neuroscientist at Oxford.

01:04:58.510 --> 01:05:01.334
And theory of mind tests
are done on children.

01:05:01.334 --> 01:05:05.240
And the theory of mind test is
some what like the following,

01:05:05.240 --> 01:05:07.490
a child is brought into a laboratory

01:05:07.490 --> 01:05:08.985
and watches a video of

01:05:08.985 --> 01:05:11.860
a child playing with some sort of toy.

01:05:11.860 --> 01:05:14.105
And then at the end of
playing with that toy

01:05:14.105 --> 01:05:17.140
they put the toy in a
drawer and they go away,

01:05:17.140 --> 01:05:21.162
and then another child comes
in and is looking around

01:05:21.162 --> 01:05:24.840
and then the experimenter asks the child

01:05:24.840 --> 01:05:27.507
who's in the experiment,
the real child and says,

01:05:27.507 --> 01:05:30.620
"You know, what does the child think?

01:05:30.620 --> 01:05:32.270
You know, what are they feeling?"

01:05:33.198 --> 01:05:35.520
And most children have a particular age,

01:05:35.520 --> 01:05:37.723
five or six or older
will say, "Oh, you know,

01:05:37.723 --> 01:05:40.767
he or she is confused, they
don't know where the toy is."

01:05:40.767 --> 01:05:42.204
Or, they'll say something that implies

01:05:42.204 --> 01:05:45.424
what we call theory of mind,
that they can put their

01:05:45.424 --> 01:05:49.985
ideas and their mind
into what the other child

01:05:49.985 --> 01:05:52.230
is likely to be feeling or experiencing.

01:05:52.230 --> 01:05:53.780
That's theory of mind.

01:05:53.780 --> 01:05:57.320
And it turns out that this is used

01:05:57.320 --> 01:05:59.930
as one of the assessments for autism,

01:05:59.930 --> 01:06:03.360
because some children,
not all, but some children

01:06:03.360 --> 01:06:05.980
that have autism or that
go on to develop autism

01:06:05.980 --> 01:06:07.660
don't have this theory of mind.

01:06:07.660 --> 01:06:10.250
They tend to fixate on the fact that

01:06:10.250 --> 01:06:12.120
the first child put the toy in the drawer.

01:06:12.120 --> 01:06:13.710
They'll say it's in the drawer

01:06:13.710 --> 01:06:15.610
as opposed to answering the question

01:06:15.610 --> 01:06:18.270
which is how does the
second child feel about it,

01:06:18.270 --> 01:06:20.620
or what are they experiencing?

01:06:20.620 --> 01:06:22.545
So theory of mind is something that

01:06:22.545 --> 01:06:25.310
emerges early in life as a part of the

01:06:25.310 --> 01:06:27.120
maturation of the circuits in the brain

01:06:27.120 --> 01:06:31.950
associated with emotional
learning and social interactions.

01:06:31.950 --> 01:06:35.500
And we experienced this in certain dreams.

01:06:35.500 --> 01:06:38.450
So if you had a dream
that you're puzzled about,

01:06:38.450 --> 01:06:40.770
or that you're fixated on
and you're thinking about,

01:06:40.770 --> 01:06:42.462
you might ask, "In that dream

01:06:42.462 --> 01:06:46.480
was I assessing somebody
else's emotion and feeling,

01:06:46.480 --> 01:06:49.720
or was I very much in my own
first person experience?"

01:06:49.720 --> 01:06:53.300
And that the tendency
is that theory of mind

01:06:53.300 --> 01:06:58.158
tends to show up most in
these REM associated dreams.

01:06:58.158 --> 01:07:00.470
Now this isn't a hard and fast rule,

01:07:00.470 --> 01:07:02.450
but chances are if you were in a dream

01:07:02.450 --> 01:07:04.470
and you were thinking about other people

01:07:04.470 --> 01:07:06.070
who wanted to do something to you,

01:07:06.070 --> 01:07:07.900
you were thinking about their desire

01:07:07.900 --> 01:07:10.730
to chase you or help you,

01:07:10.730 --> 01:07:12.700
or something that was related

01:07:12.700 --> 01:07:14.370
to someone else's emotional experience.

01:07:14.370 --> 01:07:17.001
It was probably a REM dream.

01:07:17.001 --> 01:07:19.620
That dream occurred in
rapid eye movement sleep

01:07:19.620 --> 01:07:21.660
as opposed to slow wave sleep.

01:07:21.660 --> 01:07:24.338
And that makes sense when you
think about the role of REM

01:07:24.338 --> 01:07:28.750
in emotional unlearning of associations

01:07:28.750 --> 01:07:30.100
with particular life events.

01:07:30.100 --> 01:07:33.960
That REM is rich with
all sorts of exploration

01:07:33.960 --> 01:07:37.760
of the emotional load of being chased,

01:07:37.760 --> 01:07:39.160
or the emotional load of

01:07:39.160 --> 01:07:40.890
having to take an exam the next day,

01:07:40.890 --> 01:07:42.570
or being late for something.

01:07:42.570 --> 01:07:45.430
But again, if you're fixated

01:07:45.430 --> 01:07:48.250
or you can recall thinking a lot about,

01:07:48.250 --> 01:07:49.330
or feeling a lot about

01:07:49.330 --> 01:07:51.800
what somebody else's motivations were

01:07:51.800 --> 01:07:54.260
then chances are it was in REM and if not

01:07:54.260 --> 01:07:56.780
chances are it was in slow wave sleep.

